net.automatalib.words

Interface Alphabet<I>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - symbol class.
    All Superinterfaces:
    ArrayWritable<I>, Collection<I>, Comparator<I>, Iterable<I>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    GrowingAlphabet<I>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractAlphabet, ArrayAlphabet, EnumAlphabet, FastAlphabet, ListAlphabet, SimpleAlphabet

    public interface Alphabet<I>
extends ArrayWritable<I>, Collection<I>, Comparator<I>
    Class implementing an (indexed) alphabet. An alphabet is a collection of symbols, where each symbol has a (unique) index. Apart from serving as a collection, this class also provides a one-to-one mapping between symbols and indices.
    Author:
    Malte Isberner
